This article is a statement from President Joe Biden, outlining his administration's policy to ensure that students receive a high-quality education during the COVID-19 pandemic. The policy aims to support the safe reopening and continued operation of schools, child care providers, Head Start programs, and institutions of higher education. The administration emphasizes the importance of the health and safety of students, educators, and communities, as well as the need to address educational disparities and inequities exacerbated by the pandemic. The Secretary of Education is assigned responsibilities such as providing guidance on reopening and implementing mitigation measures, while the Secretary of Health and Human Services is responsible for collecting data, ensuring equitable allocation of COVID-19-related supplies, and providing guidance and support to child care providers and Head Start programs. The Federal Communications Commission is also encouraged to increase connectivity options for students lacking reliable home broadband. The policy is to be implemented consistent with applicable law and subject to the availability of appropriations.